    <item>
      <title>About Gabe</title>
      <link>https://gabejstein.github.io/page/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gabejstein.github.io/page/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://gabejstein.github.io/images/gabe_icecream.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Gabe Stein&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Gabe is the founder of Studio Boshi and the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/@GabeStein&#34;&gt;Gabe Stein Youtube Channel&lt;/a&gt;, where he teaches game programming concepts and related things. Most of his games are made without engines and he likes to code at a low level using languages like C. He&amp;rsquo;s also been a big proponent of Lua.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;He lived in Kawasaki, Japan for 9 years before moving back to his hometown of Toronto, Canada. He&amp;rsquo;s currently developing &lt;a href=&#34;https://store.steampowered.com/app/3605940/Ocean_City_Killer/?beta=0&#34;&gt;Ocean City Killer&lt;/a&gt;, a retro cyberpunk adventure. He enjoys cycling, photography, and model making.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Game Objects and Inheritance in Lua</title>
      <link>https://gabejstein.github.io/tutorial/love2d-inheritance/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gabejstein.github.io/tutorial/love2d-inheritance/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Some people think that inheritance is impossible in Lua. It&amp;rsquo;s not a built-in feature of the language like in C++ or Java, but there&amp;rsquo;s still a way to fake it with meta-tables. This video shows one way to do it and how it can allow you to create a variety of game objects without having to rewrite a lot of code.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This video was originally published on October 30, 2024.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
